{"questionId":"4882","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urea, (H<sub>2</sub>N)<sub>2</sub>CO, is excreted by mammals and can be used as a fertilizer.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urea can also be made by the direct combination of ammonia and carbon dioxide gases.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">2NH<sub>3</sub>(g) + CO<sub>2</sub>(g) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span> (H<sub>2</sub>N)<sub>2</sub>CO(g) + H<sub>2</sub>O(g) &nbsp; &nbsp; Δ<em>H </em>&lt; 0</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the equilibrium constant expression, <em>K</em><sub>c</sub>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{K_{\\text{c}}} = \\frac{{[{{({{\\text{H}}_2}{\\text{N}})}_2}{\\text{CO}}] \\times [{{\\text{H}}_2}{\\text{O}}]}}{{{{[{\\text{N}}{{\\text{H}}_3}]}^2} \\times [{\\text{C}}{{\\text{O}}_2}]}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>K</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>c</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <msub>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>H</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>N</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>CO</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>H</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>O</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>N</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msub>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>H</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n                <mn>3</mn>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>C</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>O</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"4882","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ1.1d.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the equilibrium constant expression, Kc.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium","7.1 Equilibrium","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}